x4freetext: 1.5 MeV Van de Graaff accelerator of
Every measurement consists in detecting successively
the spectrum of recoil protons of hydrogen, the back-
ground spectrum, and that of the element under study.
With a current of deuterons on the target of
20 mu-A, a flux was obtained of about 10**8 neutrons/s
The target, in which the n,p reaction is to take place,
is placed at 7.5 cm from the neutron source and has a
diameter of 4 cm. Using a thin layer of polythene
(19.6 mg/cm 2) of 1 cm diameter as a target,
and a scintillation spectrometer in coincidence
with each other. After the triple coincidence, the
pulses are sent to a 100-channel pulse-height analyzer.
